{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "lxxe:fourth-maccabees.10",
    "translationId": "lxxe",
    "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
    "chapterNumber": 10,
    "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 10",
    "summary": "Source text for 4 Maccabees 10 in Brenton's English Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "lxxe:fourth-maccabees.10.1",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 10:1",
      "text": "Now this one, having endured this praiseworthy death, the third was brought along, and exhorted by many to taste and save his life.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:fourth-maccabees.10.2",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 10:2",
      "text": "But he cried out and said, Know ye not, that the father of those who are dead, begat me also; and that the same mother bare me; and that I was brought up in the same tenets?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:fourth-maccabees.10.3",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 10:3",
      "text": "I abjure not the noble relationship of my brethren.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:fourth-maccabees.10.4",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 10:4",
      "text": "Now then, whatever instrument of vengeance ye have, apply it to my body, for ye are not able to touch, even if ye wish it, my soul.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:fourth-maccabees.10.5",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 10:5",
      "text": "But they, highly incensed at his boldness of speech, dislocated his hands and feet with racking engines, and wrenching them from their sockets, dismembered him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:fourth-maccabees.10.6",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 10:6",
      "text": "And they dragged round his fingers, and his arms, and his legs, and his ankles.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:fourth-maccabees.10.7",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 10:7",
      "text": "And not being able by any means to strangle him, they tore off his skin, together with the extreme tips of his fingers, flayed him, and then haled him to the wheel;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:fourth-maccabees.10.8",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 10:8",
      "text": "around which his vertebral joints were loosened, and he saw his own flesh torn to shreds, and streams of blood flowing from his entrails.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:fourth-maccabees.10.9",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 10:9",
      "text": "And when about to die, he said,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:fourth-maccabees.10.10",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 10:10",
      "text": "We, O accursed tyrant, suffer this for the sake of Divine education and virtue.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:fourth-maccabees.10.11",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 10:11",
      "text": "But thou, for thine impiety and blood-shedding, shalt endure indissoluble torments.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:fourth-maccabees.10.12",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 10:12",
      "text": "And thus having died worthily of his brethren, they dragged forward the fourth, saying,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:fourth-maccabees.10.13",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 10:13",
      "text": "Do not thou share the madness of thy brethren: but give regard to the king, and save thyself.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:fourth-maccabees.10.14",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 10:14",
      "text": "But he said to them, You have not a fire so scorching as to make me play the coward.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:fourth-maccabees.10.15",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 10:15",
      "text": "By the blessed death of my brethren, and the eternal punishment of the tyrant, and the glorious life of the pious, I will not repudiate the noble brotherhood.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:fourth-maccabees.10.16",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 10:16",
      "text": "Invent, O tyrant, tortures; that you may learn, even through them, that I am the brother of those tormented before.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:fourth-maccabees.10.17",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 10:17",
      "text": "When he had said this, the blood-thirsty, and murderous, and unhallowed Antiochus ordered his tongue to be cut out.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:fourth-maccabees.10.18",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 10:18",
      "text": "But he said, Even if you take away the organ of speech, yet God hears the silent.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:fourth-maccabees.10.19",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 10:19",
      "text": "Behold, my tongue is extended, cut it off; for not for that halt thou extirpate our reasoning.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:fourth-maccabees.10.20",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 10:20",
      "text": "Gladly do we lose our limbs in behalf of God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:fourth-maccabees.10.21",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 10:21",
      "text": "But God shall speedly find you, since you cut off the tongue, the instrument of divine melody.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
